1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,840
And I hope that you are encouraged by that as well.

2
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:10,600
Psalm 25 this evening, Psalm chapter 25.

3
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:15,399
And over the next few weeks, we're planning to go through this psalm.

4
00:00:15,399 --> 00:00:21,639
And you know that for most of 2025 here on Wednesday evenings, we've had the opportunity

5
00:00:21,639 --> 00:00:23,360
to study the names of God.

6
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:28,440
And we looked at a number of those and last week, I finished up that series and I said

7
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:30,639
yes, we didn't study every name of God.

8
00:00:30,639 --> 00:00:36,919
It really was never my intention to do so, but we went through a number of them and we'll

9
00:00:36,919 --> 00:00:39,560
begin a new book study.

10
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:46,479
My pattern for all of these years of pastoring here has been to finish a series and then

11
00:00:46,479 --> 00:00:51,919
look at a psalm and kind of spend some time in a psalm and then we'll start a brand new

12
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:52,919
series.

13
00:00:52,919 --> 00:00:56,479
And so this evening, we're going to begin looking at Psalm 25.

14
00:00:56,479 --> 00:01:01,439
I plan to spend three weeks looking at this psalm and that is a psalm that's ascribed

15
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:02,520
to David.

16
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:06,919
You see sometimes, depending on the Bible that you use, they'll just have as a heading

17
00:01:06,919 --> 00:01:09,519
of a psalm, a psalm of David.

18
00:01:09,519 --> 00:01:16,620
And then other times, it may have some level of indication of maybe the timing or the circumstances

19
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:18,559
surrounding the writing.

20
00:01:18,559 --> 00:01:23,440
And for this one, it simply says a psalm of David and if you look at the context of it,

21
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:29,680
it's not completely clear as to when David is writing this psalm.

22
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:35,639
However, there are some clues that lead us to believe that it may be during the time

23
00:01:35,639 --> 00:01:41,519
of Absalom's revolt and of course, many of you would be familiar with the situation where

24
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:47,720
David was dealing with great heartache and difficulty with regard to his own son and

25
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:51,000
all the revolt and all that transpired there.

26
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,360
And what is it that would lead us to thinking that that might be the case?

27
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:59,959
Well, in verse number two, we find that David says, oh my God, I trust in Thee, let me not

28
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:00,959
be ashamed.

29
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:04,879
Notice this, let not mine enemies triumph over me.

30
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:06,919
You say, well, David had lots of enemies.

31
00:02:06,919 --> 00:02:07,919
Yes, he did.

32
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:08,919
Absolutely.

33
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:13,360
Verse 19, he says it again, consider mine enemies for they are many and they hate me

34
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,320
with cruel hatred.

35
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:19,320
And so we could say that just by looking at those two clues, that that really could be

36
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:26,199
a number of different times during David's life in which he could be penning this particular

37
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:27,199
psalm.

38
00:02:27,199 --> 00:02:32,839
However, another clue is given to us in verse number seven where the Bible says this, remember

39
00:02:32,839 --> 00:02:36,479
not the sins of my youth.

40
00:02:36,479 --> 00:02:41,440
And it would seem as if David with using the terminology that he's using there in verse

41
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:47,800
number seven would be writing this particular psalm later in life as he's saying, remember

42
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,720
not the sins of my youth.

43
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:55,880
Of course, it's not guaranteed that it is during this time of Absalom's revolt, but

44
00:02:55,880 --> 00:03:00,619
that's some clues here within the psalm that would help us understand.

45
00:03:00,619 --> 00:03:05,080
We know that even if it were not specifically the time of Absalom's revolt, that there's

46
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:11,139
time here where he's talking about his enemies and these enemies are many.

47
00:03:11,139 --> 00:03:16,679
And so we know that David is dealing with some hardship, he's dealing with some difficulty

48
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:19,520
as he's writing Psalm 25.

49
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:25,979
And it's interesting to me because as we examine the psalm, and I've kind of taken three parts

50
00:03:25,979 --> 00:03:29,699
and this is what we'll deal with over the next three weeks, but I believe that it really

51
00:03:29,699 --> 00:03:35,880
reveals to us that David in this psalm, he's longing for three things.

52
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:42,539
And I believe that the psalm reveals to us that he's longing for peace, he's longing

53
00:03:42,539 --> 00:03:47,419
for direction, and he's longing for forgiveness.

54
00:03:47,419 --> 00:03:51,899
And I think about those three things that David is longing for, and tonight we'll deal

55
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:52,899
with the first one.

56
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:56,899
I've titled the message, A Longing for Peace.

57
00:03:56,899 --> 00:04:01,380
And I think about the peace, direction, and forgiveness that David is longing for as you

58
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:08,520
study through Psalm 25, and we begin to understand that with the hardship that David is facing,

59
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:13,880
the circumstances that he's dealing with, it's brought him to a place where he's longing

60
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:17,959
for peace and for direction and for forgiveness.

61
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:23,119
It leads him to a time of examination because he's dealing with this hardship.

62
00:04:23,119 --> 00:04:29,079
And I begin to think about our own lives and the reality is that sometimes we face difficulties.

63
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:35,299
We have circumstances that are adverse and we face those things and we begin to look

64
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:41,339
at what is it that we should do during those times of difficulty and adversity.

65
00:04:41,339 --> 00:04:44,619
And there are times in which, no doubt, we wish it would just go away.

66
00:04:44,619 --> 00:04:49,920
I don't have time for this, I don't want to deal with this, God, what are you doing?

67
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,299
Whatever it might be.

68
00:04:51,299 --> 00:04:58,619
But the truth is that God has, in times like what David is facing here in Psalm 25, God

69
00:04:58,619 --> 00:05:05,859
has and uses these times in the lives of his people to grow us and to develop us.

70
00:05:05,859 --> 00:05:10,859
And we find that David is longing for peace, he's longing for direction, he's longing for

71
00:05:10,859 --> 00:05:15,579
forgiveness and one of the things that I'll mention each week as we look through this

72
00:05:15,579 --> 00:05:20,920
Psalm that I'm so thankful for and I hope that you would rejoice in this reality this

73
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:30,440
evening as well, and that is that David knew where to go for peace, direction, and forgiveness.

74
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:34,519
Aren't you thankful that you know the God who is the God of all peace?

75
00:05:34,519 --> 00:05:40,559
Aren't you thankful that you know the God that says, I will guide you, I will lead you?

76
00:05:40,559 --> 00:05:44,640
Aren't you thankful that you know the God that says that he's ready to pardon, that

77
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:46,480
he will forgive?

78
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:51,859
And when you go through, when you face trials and difficulties in your life, when I face

79
00:05:51,859 --> 00:05:59,579
difficulties and trials in my life, just as David is here in Psalm 25, we need the peace

80
00:05:59,579 --> 00:06:01,959
that God can give us.

81
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:05,299
And we must run to God to get that peace.

82
00:06:05,299 --> 00:06:06,880
We need direction.

83
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,880
There are times in which we say, I don't know what to do.

84
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:14,779
God will guide us and he'll teach us, he'll lead us.

85
00:06:14,779 --> 00:06:20,799
And also causes us to examine ourselves, Lord, if there be any wicked way in me, Lord, help

86
00:06:20,799 --> 00:06:27,640
